article_title: Man leaps to death from George Washington Bridge, lands on railway
article_text:
A man dressed in black jumped to his death from the George Washington Bridge Sunday night, a Port Authority spokeswoman said.

A civilian witnessed the man leap at 8:09 p.m., and land on the Amtrak railway on the New York side of the bridge, the spokeswoman said,

Officials found the man's body at 8:20 p.m. His identity was not immediately released.
